<title>CANADA: Canada March bankruptcies rise over year.</title>
<headline>Canada March bankruptcies rise over year.</headline>
<dateline>OTTAWA 1997-05-23</dateline>
<text>
<p>Bankruptcies in Canada rose to 8,147 in March from 7,775 a year earlier, the Department of Consumer and Corporate Affairs said on Friday.</p>
<p>The department said 1,061 businesses and 7,086 consumers went bankrupt in the month.</p>
<p>In February, 8,450 bankruptcies were recorded.</p>
<p>For the year to date, 24,470 bankruptcies have been registered (3,322 businesses and 21,148 consumers), up from 23,047 in the same period last year.</p>
<p>((Reuters Ottawa Bureau, 613-235-6745))</p>
